taffordshire, England","Malpas, Cheshire, England":"Malpas, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Montalt","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Salvatore, Vito, Angelo, Carmine, Domenico, Giovanni, Sal, Agostino, Alessandra, Alessia, Antonio, Emilio, Franco.","Italian: habitational name from any of various places calledMontalto or Montaldo, especially Montalto Uffugo in Cosenza province.","Portuguese: habitational name from a place called Montalto, from <i>monte</i> ‘hill’ + <i>alto</i> ‘high’ (from Latin <i>altus</i>)."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Beatrix","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From a Late Latin personal name, which was borne by a saint martyred in Rome, together with Saints Faustinus and Simplicius, in the early 4th century. The original form of the name was probably <i>Viatrix</i>, a feminine version of <i>Viator</i> ‘voyager (through life)’, which was a favourite name among early Christians. This was then altered by association with Latin <i>Beatus</i> ‘blessed’ (<i>Via-</i> and <i>Bea-</i> sometimes being pronounced the same in Late Latin).  See also  Beatrice ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Beatrix Montalt was born in 1182, in Cheshire, England, United Kingdom, her father, Baron Robert Monhout, was 19 and her mother, Nichole de Rising, was 8. She had at least 2 sons with William de Malpas. She lived in Flintshire, Wales, United Kingdom in 1182. She died in 1245, at the age of 63."},"et":{"1182–1245":"1182–1245","1190–1252":"1190–1252","1210–1255":"1210–1255","1225–1279":"1225–1279","1163–1229":"1163–1229","1175–1231":"1175–1231","1190":"1190","1231":"1231","1175":"1175","1252":"1252","1163":"1163","1182":"1182","1225":"1225","1279":"1279","1245":"1245","Abt 1210":"umbes 1210","1255":"1255","Abt 1231":"umbes 1231","1210":"1210",